gins can remove&#10;inappropriate ones depending on the situation or user making edits.&#10;Specifically because without filtering anyone with the edit_users&#10;capability can edit others to be administrators, even if they are&#10;only editors or authors. This filter allows admins to delegate&#10;user management.&#10;&#10;@since 2.8&#10;&#10;@return unknown" ilk="function" line="183" lineend="190" name="get_editable_roles" returns="unknown" signature="unknown get_editable_roles()"><variable citdl="wp_roles.roles" line="186" name="all_roles" /><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="184" name="wp_roles" /><variable citdl="apply_filters()" line="187" name="editable_roles" /></scope><scope doc="Retrieve user data and filter it.&#10;&#10;@since 2.0.5&#10;&#10;@param int $user_id User ID.&#10;@return object WP_User object with user data." ilk="function" line="200" lineend="206" name="get_user_to_edit" returns="object" signature="object get_user_to_edit(int $user_id)"><variable citdl="int" ilk="argument" line="200" name="user_id" /><variable citdl="get_userdata()" line="201" name="user" /></scope><scope doc="Retrieve the user's drafts.&#10;&#10;@since 2.0.0&#10;&#10;@param int $user_id User ID.&#10;@return array" ilk="function" line="216" lineend="221" name="get_users_drafts" returns="array" signature="array get_users_drafts(int $user_id)"><variable citdl="int" ilk="argument" line="216" name="user_id" /><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="217" name="wpdb" /><variable citdl="wpdb.prepare()" line="218" name="query" /></scope><scope doc="Remove user and optionally reassign posts and links to another user.&#10;&#10;If the $reassign parameter is not assigned to an User ID, then all posts will&#10;be deleted of that user. The action 'delete_user' that is passed the User ID&#10;being deleted will be run after the posts are either reassigned or deleted.&#10;The user meta will also be deleted that are for that User ID.&#10;&#10;@since 2.0.0&#10;&#10;@param i